---

üîπ General Note ‚Äì Location Name Column

Across all tabs, please ensure:

Do not fill ‚ÄúLocation Name‚Äù unless you are certain.

If provided, use strictly: <CLLICODE> <space> <Room Name>
Example: NWBLWICZ Switch Room 1 100.
DC Track automatically derives this value from the Location* column, so incorrect entries may cause load issues.



---

AC ASSETS

1. UPS

What needs to be filled:

Status must be Planned or Installed (site survey had ‚ÄúFalse‚Äù).

Output Wiring: confirm if it is truly 3-wire; holistic template default is 4-wire + Ground, so please validate.

Custom Field ‚ÄúUPS Maintained By‚Äù: leave this blank.



---

2. UPS Bank

Required corrections:

Status must be Planned/Installed (not blank).

Naming convention:

If UPS is UPS A1, then UPS Bank should be UPSBank-A1.


Output wiring: verify whether 3-wire is correct.

Rating (Amps) must align correctly:

UPS Bank Rating A ‚â• UPS KW rating, and

UPS Bank Rating A ‚â• total load of PDUs fed from it.




---

3. Load Devices (UPS ‚Üí UPS Bank & UPS Bank ‚Üí PDU)

These were already fully described in yesterday‚Äôs clarification document.
Please continue using that guidance.
Load Devices should follow:

UPS ‚Üí UPS Bank ‚Üí Line Side = Extension, Load Side = Bus

UPS Bank ‚Üí PDU ‚Üí Line Side = Bus, Load Side = Extension

Naming convention:

For UPS to UPS Bank: UPSName BREAKER

For UPS Bank to PDU: PDUName BREAKER


Source format:
UPSBankName / <Load Device Name>



---

4. PDU

Two corrections required:

1. Power Fed From must be UPS Bank (not the UPS itself).


2. Source must follow:
UPSBankName / <Load Device Name>
The sample in the first screenshot of your message is the correct reference.




---

5. PDU Panel

Issues to correct:

Number of poles: 3 is acceptable, but since these are dummy panels, 6 poles is preferred.

Panel Layout: should generally be Two Column.

Pole Numbering:

If Two Column ‚Üí use Odd/Even

If One Column ‚Üí Sequential is fine.


First Pole Number: should be 1 for every panel (not 1, 7, 10, 4, etc.).

Panel Naming:

Panel 1 ‚Üí PDU-A11 Panel 1

Panel 2 ‚Üí PDU-A11 Panel 2

Pair 1 ‚Üí PDU-A11 SPARE 1

Pair 2 ‚Üí PDU-A11 SPARE 2




---

6. PDU Panel Breakers

Please apply the following:

Remove the incorrect row containing ATS ‚Üí UPS connection.
PDUs never directly feed UPS, so this row should not exist.

If RPP is attached:

Object = Breaker to Panel


If no sub-panel location provided & status = open:

Object = Breaker to Others


Ensure the Panel name matches the corrected PDU Panel names above.



---

RPP ASSETS

7. RPP Panel

No changes required ‚Äî the entries are correct.


---

8. RPP Panel Breakers

If Cabinet is attached AND state = Closed ‚Üí Object = Breaker to Cabinet
(Additional cabinet columns will appear for such entries.)

If no cabinet attached or state is not closed ‚Üí Object = Breaker to Others
Everything else looks fine.



---

DC ASSETS

9. DC Plant Panel & DC Plant Panel Breakers

These fields are mandatory since BDFB/BDFB Panels cannot be completed without specifying:
Plant / Plant Panel : Plant Panel Breaker
Please update these values wherever missing.


---

10. Load Devices for DC

Same logic as UPS/UPS Bank load devices.
Use the explanation document shared yesterday.


---

11. HVAC

Two mandatory fields missing in the site survey:

Cooling Zone Name

Sensible Capacity


Please ensure both fields are added for each HVAC unit.


